description: Bigby Wolf takes center stage in what might be the most action-packed FABLES story to date. Bigby embarks on a quest through the American Heartland to find a new location for Fabletown. In his wanderings, Bigby stumbles across a small town named Story City, that, amazingly enough, seems to be populated by werewolves. Who are they and where did they come from? They aren't Fables, but they sure aren't normal mundys. They seem to already know and revere Bigby, but at the same time they've captured and caged him - but why? Unravelling the many mysteries of Story City may cost Bigby more than his life.

description: It's the ULTIMATE AMAZING SPIDER-MAN EVENT OF THE YEAR, as Spider-Man comes face-to-face with...Spider-Man! Can even Peter Parker and Miles Morales - the Spider-Men of two worlds - defeat Mysterio, the Master of Illusions? What happens when Miles encounters an older, wiser version of his inspiration, Peter Parker? And what will both Spider-Men do now that they know they're not alone in the universe? Guest-starring Nick Fury and the Ultimates! Be here for the story that makes history, as Brian Michael Bendis tears down the walls between the Marvel Universe and the Ultimate Universe! Collecting SPIDER-MEN #1-5.

description: It's cross-realm rivalry when the Scare School's cherished Spookalympics trophy is stolen by rival Petrified Prep Elementary! Casper and the gang go all out to get it back, but there's more to this "theft" than meets the eye! Also, when Thatch is made Scare School hall monitor, he rules the school with an iron fist! Can anyone challenge the authority of the power mad vampire?

Nick Archer isn't much of a detective, but he's managed to get himself one pretty sweet surveillance gig: once a week he sends a jealous millionaire the photos that prove his wife is faithful, leaving Nick plenty of free nights to spend making a liar of both himself and the client's wife.

But when the client turns up dead, his cheating wife is the prime suspect and it's up to Nick to clear her, except Nick has connections to this case that go deeper than anyone realizes.

description:
The final volume of the acclaimed crime series brings together all the threads laid out from the very beginning for a dramatic conclusion years in the making! Collecting SCALPED #56-60.

Back Blurb

THE FINAL CHAPTER OF A MODERN CRIME MASTERPIECE

Mission accomplished.

Chief Red Crow is in jail, his drug operation in ruins, his iron grip on the Prairie Rose Reservation broken forever. It only took a betrayal by the man he trusted most to make it happen.

Special Agent Dash Bad Horse survived his time undercover as Red Crow's right hand with his life, and most of his soul, intact. Now he's free --- free to quit the FBI, free to make up for his old sins, free to leave the Rez behind...or stay and make a better life.

Or so he thinks.

Red Crow may be in prison, but he still knows secrets that could take Dash down. The young men swept up in Red Crow and Bad Horse's war are still out there, hungry for payback. And the hidden killer who started it all and is still unpunished, the trail of bodies behind him growing longer by the day.

These men are headed for a final showdown. Decades of deceit, betrayal, and murder are coming to a head. When the smoke clears, will any of them be left standing --- or have they all reached the end of the trail?

Acclaimed creators Jason Aaron and R.M. Guéra present SCALPED: TRAIL'S END --- the explosive conclusion of their Native American noir epic. This collectino includes issues #56-60, R.M. Guéra sketches from throught the series' run, and an afterword by Jason Aaron.

description:
Jaime Reyes is the new Blue Beetle in this title collecting issues #1-6 of the DC COMICS - THE NEW 52 series!

Can this teen hero turn an alien weapon of mass destruction into a force for good? And can he protect the scarab from the Super-Villains who want it for their own nefarious purposes?

Back Blurb

IT'S NOT EASY BEING BLUE

Jaime Reyes has all the burdens of a typical teenager. He worries about school, girls, his popularity, and the sentient alien technology that has loaded itself in his spine and may want to take over Earth. Y'know, your average high-school issues.

Since accidentally becoming host to this big blue alien bug, Jaime can turn into an armored, flying space soldier. But these new abilities are not always in his control. The scarab isn't just a suit of armor --- it's alive. The alien consciousness is always there, giving him instructions. If Jaime doesn't follow its orders, the scarab can simply take control of his suit and force to comply.

The scarab will use its host to attack anyone who threatens its mission, including Jaime's friends and family. Can Jaime learn to control his "bugsuit" before he puts everyone in his life at rick?

TONY BERARD (GREEN LANTERN CORPS) and IG GUARA (TEEN TITANS) revamp the Blue Beetle in stunning fashion in BLUE BEETLE: METAMORPHOSIS (collecting issues #1-6).
name: Volume 1
